This paper discusses the performance of state-of-the-art reading comprehension models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of specialized neural components, which suggests that it may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as these sub-categories are related to NLP and machine learning.
